main.name: Nathan Moeller
main.description: I am a software engineer currently working for IBM in San Jose. I am originally from the midwest, where I attended school at the University of Wisconsin - Madison and the University of Minnesota - Twin Cities.
main.bio: Software engineer and soccer player. Shoot me an email to find out more about me!
main.contactmessage: Here is where you should write your message to readers to have them get in contact with you.

education.description: While in graudate school I took a variety of classes including Artificial Intelligence, machine learning, robotics, and experimental games. After taking software engineering and a class called "Developing the Interactive Web", I decided I wanted to pursue software engineering as a career.
While in undergraduate school I took many classes to grow my knowledge and interest in computer science. I really enjoyed taking classes like algorithms, graphics, and database systems.

projects.name: Bounty Streamer
projects.description: Bounty Streamer is a web application designed for twith streaming where viewers can incentivize streamers to complete in game challenges for real money. We developed this project as a team a 3 and used a Java Spring backend, React frontend and PayPal/Twitch/AWS REST APIs and services.

projects.name: Word Affects
projects.description: Word Affects is a twitter seniment analysis web application that we developed for the UW Madison 2014 CS NEST competition. For this project we won 3rd place for implementing a Naive Bayes classifier and a web interface to see a real time classification of tweets.

projects.name: The Infected Dungeon Game
projects.description: The Infected Dungeon Game is a game I made in Unity for Experimental Games and Technologies. It is a first person survival shooter game that adjusts in difficulty to the player's skill level.

projects.name: Focused Web Crawler Classifier
projects.description: For class "Intelligent Agents" in graduate school, I implemented a neural network classifier to detect patent related web pages to use in a focused web crawler. For this project I worked by myself and coded in Python.
